Constants are fixed values that do not change during program execution. They make code more readable and maintainable.

ğŸ“Š Types of Constants

1. ğŸ”¢ Numeric Constants
These represent fixed numerical values and are classified as:

ğŸ§® a) Integer Constants
Whole numbers without a decimal point.
